  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(localBusinessSchema)} />
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-8 pt-16 pb-24">
    <header class="mb-8">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <span class="bg-primary/20 text-primary font-label font-bold text-xs uppercase tracking-widest px-3 py-1 rounded-full">{post.category}</span>
        <time class="font-body text-sm text-secondary">{post.date}</time>
      </div>
      <h1 class="font-headline text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tighter text-on-surface mb-4">{post.title}</h1>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed">{post.description}</p>
    </header>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Industrial machinery — CNC machines, printing presses, production equipment, hydraulic systems — often represents a substantial investment. Damage during transport due to inadequate packaging can mean costly repairs, downtime, and disappointed customers.
      </p>
      <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed">
        Honeycomb cardboard panels provide superior protection while remaining lightweight and cost-effective. This guide covers how manufacturing and industrial companies in Malaysia use honeycomb packaging to safeguard valuable machinery during shipping.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-on-surface mb-6">1. Why Honeycomb Beats Standard Cardboard for Machinery</h2>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-lg font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Superior Strength-to-Weight Ratio</h3>
      <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Honeycomb cardboard uses a hollow hexagonal structure that distributes force efficiently. This design provides:
      </p>

      <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-primary font-bold">✓</span>
          <span class="font-body text-on-surface"><span class="font-bold">3–5× the compression strength</span> of standard corrugated cardboard</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-primary font-bold">✓</span>
          <span class="font-body text-on-surface"><span class="font-bold">Low weight</span> — honeycomb is 50–70% air, reducing shipping costs</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-primary font-bold">✓</span>
          <span class="font-body text-on-surface"><span class="font-bold">Impact absorption</span> — the honeycomb structure flexes and absorbs shock without transferring force to contents</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="text-primary font-bold">✓</span>
          <span class="font-body text-on-surface"><span class="font-bold">Consistent protection</span> — no weak points; uniform strength across the entire panel</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-lg font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Real-World Example</h3>
      <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed">
        A Selangor-based printing press manufacturer shipping 2-ton machines to Singapore typically requires 6–8 layers of corrugated cardboard for adequate protection. By switching to 20mm honeycomb panels, they reduced material layers to 2–3 panels, cutting weight by 40% while improving protection. This saved transport costs and reduced damage claims.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-on-surface mb-6">2. Sizing & Panel Thickness Guide for Machinery</h2>

      <div class="bg-surface-variant/50 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Choosing Panel Thickness</h3>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <p class="font-bold text-on-surface text-sm mb-2">10–15mm Panels (Light machinery, 500–2,000 kg)</p>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm">For smaller equipment, motors, and generators. Cost-effective and adequate for short-distance shipping.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="border-t border-outline-variant/20 pt-4">
            <p class="font-bold text-on-surface text-sm mb-2">20–25mm Panels (Medium machinery, 2,000–5,000 kg)</p>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm">Most common for manufacturing equipment, CNC machines, and printing presses. Recommended for long-distance domestic or regional shipping.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="border-t border-outline-variant/20 pt-4">
            <p class="font-bold text-on-surface text-sm mb-2">30–40mm Panels (Heavy equipment, 5,000+ kg)</p>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm">For ultra-sensitive or extremely valuable machinery. Used when transit involves multiple transfers or rough handling is expected.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-lg font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Panel Configuration</h3>
      <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-4">
        For machinery shipping, panels are typically arranged as:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 mb-6">
        <li class="font-body text-on-surface">• <span class="font-bold">Base layer</span> — 1–2 panels supporting the equipment weight</li>
        <li class="font-body text-on-surface">• <span class="font-bold">Side protection</span> — panels on all four sides (corners critical)</li>
        <li class="font-body text-on-surface">• <span class="font-bold">Top cover</span> — protective panels or corrugated cover</li>
        <li class="font-body text-on-surface">• <span class="font-bold">Padding layers</span> — thin foam or paper sheets between machinery and panels</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-on-surface mb-6">3. Custom Design & Assembly Process</h2>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-lg font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Working with Quinocycle on Custom Solutions</h3>

      <ol class="space-y-4 mb-6">
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="font-bold text-primary text-lg">1</span>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-bold text-on-surface mb-2">Measure Equipment</h4>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm">Provide exact length, width, height, and weight of machinery. Include any delicate features (control panels, moving parts) that need extra protection.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="font-bold text-primary text-lg">2</span>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-bold text-on-surface mb-2">Panel Calculation</h4>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm">Quinocycle calculates the exact number, size, and thickness of panels needed. Standard practice: add 10–15cm clearance on all sides for padding.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="font-bold text-primary text-lg">3</span>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-bold text-on-surface mb-2">Custom Cutting</h4>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm">Panels are cut to fit your equipment precisely. Custom die-cuts for irregular shapes are available (rush fees apply).</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="font-bold text-primary text-lg">4</span>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-bold text-on-surface mb-2">Assembly Support</h4>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm">Quinocycle can provide assembly instructions or arrange on-site assembly for large orders.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-on-surface mb-6">4. Cost-Benefit Analysis: Why Honeycomb Makes Financial Sense</h2>

      <div class="p-8 bg-primary/5 border border-primary/20 rounded-lg mb-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Example: Protecting a RM 150,000 CNC Machine</h3>
        <table class="w-full text-sm mb-6">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-outline-variant/20">
              <th class="text-left font-bold text-on-surface py-2">Cost Factor</th>
              <th class="text-left font-bold text-on-surface py-2">Standard Cardboard</th>
              <th class="text-left font-bold text-on-surface py-2">Honeycomb</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="border-b border-outline-variant/20">
