              <td class="py-2 text-on-surface">8–12%</td>
              <td class="py-2 text-on-surface">1–2%</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 text-on-surface">Expected repair cost</td>
              <td class="py-2 text-on-surface">RM 12,000–18,000</td>
              <td class="py-2 text-on-surface">RM 1,500–3,000</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm">
          <span class="font-bold">Total cost with honeycomb:</span> RM 1,450 + RM 2,000 expected repairs = RM 3,450<br>
          <span class="font-bold">Total cost with standard:</span> RM 1,400 + RM 15,000 expected repairs = RM 16,400<br>
          <span class="font-bold">Savings with honeycomb:</span> RM 12,950 per shipment
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed">
        For high-value machinery, honeycomb packaging is not an expense — it's insurance that pays for itself by preventing costly damage.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-on-surface mb-6">FAQ: Honeycomb Cardboard for Machinery</h2>

      <details class="mb-4 p-4 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg group">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-bold text-on-surface flex justify-between items-center">
          How much protection does honeycomb cardboard provide vs. standard cardboard?
          <span class="transition-transform group-open:rotate-180">▼</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Honeycomb cardboard is 3–5× stronger than standard corrugated cardboard while being significantly lighter. It distributes impact force over a wider area, making it ideal for heavy machinery.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="mb-4 p-4 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg group">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-bold text-on-surface flex justify-between items-center">
          What thickness of honeycomb is needed for machinery shipping?
          <span class="transition-transform group-open:rotate-180">▼</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          For machinery, 15–25mm honeycomb panels are typical. Thicker panels (up to 40mm) may be used for ultra-sensitive equipment. The choice depends on equipment weight and fragility.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="mb-4 p-4 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg group">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-bold text-on-surface flex justify-between items-center">
          Can honeycomb cardboard be customized for specific equipment?
          <span class="transition-transform group-open:rotate-180">▼</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Yes. Honeycomb panels can be cut to fit any machinery dimension. Many industrial companies work with Quinocycle to design custom protective shells for unique equipment.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="mb-4 p-4 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg group">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-bold text-on-surface flex justify-between items-center">
          Is honeycomb packaging more expensive than standard boxes?
          <span class="transition-transform group-open:rotate-180">▼</span>
        </summary>
